<p itemprop="description">A principal performance analyst provides expert leadership in organisational performance measurement and improvement. They define performance strategy, establish enterprise-wide performance capabilities, and drive transformational change in how performance is measured and managed.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define strategic vision and approach for organisational performance measurement</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead enterprise-wide performance transformation initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish performance management as a core organisational capability</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide expert advice to executive leadership on performance strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in performance measurement methodologies and tools</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build performance analysis capability and talent development programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in performance management communities and best practice networks</li>
    </ul>
</section>

